// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`output formats > renders a stable human scorecard 1`] = `
"  actlint  ▸  -                                                 honesty grade: F
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  1 tool scanned · 1 under-declared · 0 undeclared · 0 over-declared

  ✖ CRIT  exec_sql  write-as-readonly
      The tool declares readOnlyHint: true, but its action is derived as mutating (from the signals shape.freeform-code-input, verb.execute). A read-only declaration on a tool that writes suppresses the confirmation a spec-conformant client would otherwise show.
      ↳ OWASP ASI02:2026, ASI03:2026 · OWASP MCP02:2025 · CoSAI MCP-T9 · EU AI Act Art.14, Art.15 · NIST AI-RMF:MEASURE · MCP field readOnlyHint

  advisories — capability hygiene, not honesty verdicts
  ◐ ADV   exec_sql  freeform-input-as-code
      The input schema accepts an unconstrained free-form parameter interpreted as code (from the signal shape.freeform-code-input). There is no MCP hint for this; it is a capability-hygiene note that the parameter lets a caller drive arbitrary behavior.
      ↳ OWASP ASI05:2026 · OWASP MCP05:2025 · CoSAI MCP-T3 · EU AI Act Art.15 · NIST AI-RMF:MANAGE
  ◐ ADV   exec_sql  no-scope-constraint
      This is a sensitive action (destructiveness mutating, reach unknown) whose input schema carries no narrowing constraint — no enum, pattern, format, or limit bounds its parameters. A tighter schema would scope what the tool can be asked to do.
      ↳ OWASP ASI02:2026 · OWASP MCP02:2025 · CoSAI MCP-T3 · EU AI Act Art.15 · NIST AI-RMF:MANAGE
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  0 of 1 tool consistent.
  Full report: --json
"
`;
